@node "wstep" "What is savED ?"

  In few words: savED is HEX editor. You can use it to modify savegames.
It replaces few programs, editor like in FileMaster and calculator (and
maybe more).

savED is SHARWARE. Please read about it's @{"copyright" link "prawa"} and how to @{"register" link "rejestracja"}.

Features:
   - GUI is font-sensitive
   - you can change screen (public or own)
   - you can change font (only fixed-width)
   - you can change screen palette, font and cursor colours
   - searching:
         - in ANSI
         - in HEX
         - for letters and numbers
(*)      - for words
(*)- replacing and counting
   - calc with HEX->DEC and DEC->HEX.
   - undo and redo
   - it uses reqtools.library to choose file, screen and font
      (ReqTools is Copyright (c) Nico François and Magnus Holmgren)
(*)- copy, cut and paste
(*)- you change size of file, by moving beg or end of file
   - it's VERY EASY
   - savED will be updated and supported in future
   - ...

(*) - NEW

@endnode

@node "wymagania" "Requirements"

   - Amiga :)
   - kickstart >=2.0.
   - reqtools.library >=38
         (ReqTools is Copyright (c) Nico François and Magnus Holmgren.)

@endnode

@node "instalacja" "Installation"

	Copy savED's dir where you want and if you don't have reqtools.library
in LIBS:, then copy it from saved/libs.

SavED 1.1 needs savED.cs for regular work. It must be in savED's dir or
in S: or in ENV:.


@endnode
@node "obsluga" "Usage"

@{"General           " link "podstawy"}
@{"Pull down menus   " link "menu"}

@endnode
@node "podstawy" "General"

You can run savED from Shell/CLI or Workbench.

@{b}Workbench:@{ub}
Tooltypes:
 FILE = file
 PREFSFILE = file.prefs
Both aren't necessary.

@{b}CLI/Shell:@{ub}

savED FILE,PREFSFILE=PREFS/K

 FILE
ex.  savED Civ033.sav

 PREFSFILE=PREFS
ex.  savED PREFSFILE Work:savEDbackup.prefs
or   savED PREFS ENVARC:savED.prefs



++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

 SavED's window looks somethink like this::

#SavED 1.0############################################################I II I
|Civ0001.sav              HEX 172/$AC P:111/$6F   L:3590/$E06              #
|00000000  00 11 22 43 23 65 11 EF A2 BA EB 00 00 30 68  .."C#e.......0h   #
|00000015  00 11 0F B2 0A 3B DB 84 88 0D 31 54 8F C9 42  .....;....1T..B   #
|\_____/   \__________________________________________/  \_____________/   #
|   |                               |                           |          #
|number of first offset          hex part                  ASCII part      #
|in line                                                                 __#
________________________________________________________________________|/||


Status bar:
ex.
Civ0001.sav             HEX    172/$AC     P:111/$6F   L:3590/$E06              
   |                    \_/    \_____/      \_______/  \_________/
 file                   /         |              \            |
             edit mode        dec/hex value    offset     file length



@{b}Editing in HEX mode:@{ub}
 - enter first figure (0-F)
 - cursor will change colour (you can change it in prefs)
 - enter secund figure (0-F)

@{b}Editing in ASC mode:@{ub}
 - like in CED (only overwriting , NOT insert).

You can change edit mode, by pressing TAB or by pull-down menu (see @{"menus" link "edit"}).

@endnode
